```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(col, r"[^a-zA-Z0-9]" => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to convert the string to lowercase, and then `replace` with a regular expression that matches any character that is not a letter or number. The replacement is an underscore (`"_"`). This ensures that all non-alphanumeric characters are replaced with underscores, including spaces and hyphens.
